<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>netstandard2.0</TargetFramework>
    <GeneratePackageOnBuild>true</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
    <Version>0.9.0</Version>
    <Company>AlexanderOnTest.tech</Company>
    <Authors>Alexander Dunn</Authors>
    <Product>NetCoreWebDriverFactory</Product>
    <Description>A library to ease the creation of Selenium WebDriver instances in .net Core projects.</Description>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>First release: 5 October 2018
Local and Remote WebDriver creation made easy
Usage:
Add Nuget Packages for the Browser drivers. 
(tested with the Selenium.WebDriver.xxxx packages by jsakamoto)
IWebDriver localWebDriver = StaticWebDriverFactory.GetLocalWebDriver(Browser.Firefox);
or 
IWebDriver remoteWebDriver = StaticWebDriverFactory.GetRemoteWebDriver(Browser.Chrome, gridUri, Platform.Linux);

Supported Browsers:
Chrome
Firefox
Edge (Windows 10 version 1803 Only)
Internet Explorer 11 (Windows Platforms)
Safari

Platforms:
Windows
Linux
MacOS

Tested and working on Windows 10 and Linux.
It SHOULD work on MacOS (at least for Firefox and Chrome) but is currently untested.

The repository at
https://github.com/AlexanderOnTesting/NetCoreWebDriverFactory
contains test projects for Windows Linux and MacOS
These can be used to test your setup and demonstrate the options available.</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <Copyright>Copyright 2018 Alexander Dunn</Copyright>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/AlexanderOnTesting/NetCoreWebDriverFactory</PackageProjectUrl>
    <PackageLicenseUrl>https://github.com/AlexanderOnTesting/NetCoreWebDriverFactory/blob/master/LICENSE</PackageLicenseUrl>
    <PackageTags>Selenium, WebDriverFactory, WebDriver, Selenium WebDriver, DotNet Core, .net Core.</PackageTags>
    <PackageId>Selenium.WebDriver.NetCoreWebDriverFactory</PackageId>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Selenium.WebDriver" Version="3.14.0" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
